-- Ford CEO says on plan for profit in 2009
-- 
-- Wed Aug 8, 2007 11:56am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/08/us-ford-ceo-idUSN0821765620070808

 

 TRAVERSE CITY, Mich  (Reuters) - Ford Motor Co. ( F.N ), which is in the midst of a sweeping restructuring, is on track to return to profitability in 2009, Chief Executive Alan Mulally said on Wednesday. 

 "We're going to make progress and have less of a loss than we had year-over-year," Mulally said at an industry conference. "And we're on our plan for 2008 (to) return to profitability in 2009." "I'm very encouraged by the progress that everyone is making by pulling together around this plan," he added. (Reporting by  Poornima Gupta )